Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Cm-CATH1 (C. mydas cathelicidin 1; natural AMPs; turtle, reptiles, marine animals; UCLL1a)

Literature Information.Literature: Sequence analysis: APD analysis reveals that the sequence of the peptide shows 48.8% similarity toalligator cathelicidin As-CATH4.Activity: Active against Gram- E. coli ATCC25922 (MIC 9.3 ug/mL), some clinical strains (MIC 4.69 - >200 ug/mL), S. dysenteriae (4.69 ug/ml), K. Pneumoniae (MIC 75- >200 ug/ml), S. maltophilia (MIC 9.38 ug/mL),  P. aeruginosa clinical strain (MIC 4.69 ug/ml),  Gram+ S. aureus clinical strains (MIC 18.75-75 ug/ml), B. cereus (MIC 75 ug/ml), B. subtilis (MIC 18.75 ug/ml), E. faecium,  N. asteroides (MIC 4.69 ug/ml), fungi C. albicans (MIC 1.17- >200 ug/ml), aquatic pathogens V. brasiliensis (MIC 18.7 ug/ml), V. cholerae (37.5 ug/ml), A. veronii (MIC 75 ug/ml), E. tarda (MIC 18.75 ug/ml).
Literature Information.Author: Qiao X, Yang H, Gao J, Zhang F, Chu P, Yang Y, Zhang M, Wang Y, Yu H.2019
